# Improved version
Of all the subjects I studied at school, Mathematics has always been my favorite. I started learning it in primary school as part of my formal education, just like every other student. At first, we focused on basic arithmetic, but as I moved on to secondary school, the subject became more challenging with algebra, geometry, and more complex problem-solving.
To be honest, I wasn't very fond of Maths when I was a child because I found it unnecessarily complicated. I used to struggle with formulas and long calculations, and sometimes I felt overwhelmed. However, as I grew older, I gradually began to appreciate it. I realized that Mathematics - it actually plays a vital role in many aspects of our daily lives.
Math lessons were usually quite structured and logical. Our teacher would explain a concept, give some examples, and then we would practice solving problems either individually or in groups. What I enjoyed most was the sense of achievement I felt when I finally solved a difficult question after thinking about it for a while. It really boosted my confidence.
What makes Mathematics special, in my opinion, is that it trains you to think logically and systematically. It improves problem-solving skills and helps develop patience and attention to detail. Many people believe that Maths is only for gifted students, but I strongly disagree. I think everyone can benefit from having at least a basic understanding of mathematical concepts. For example, geometry is essential when designing and building a house, while arithmetic is necessary for managing personal finances and calculating daily expenses.
Overall, although Mathematics can sometimes be challenging, I find it incredibly rewarding. It not only sharpens my mind but also helps me see the world in a more logical and organized way. That's why it remains my favorite subject.

