In my country, it is compulsory to teach all students Maths when they join grade school. I was taught many math skills such as addition, subtraction, multiplication, division and etc. I would like to talk about counting because this skill lays the foundation for all other mathematical operations.
I vividly remember first coming to know counting skill in the first year of elementary school, when I was 6 years old. My teacher showed us a group of popsicle sticks and asked us to count them. Sometimes, we were taught to count on our fingertips. These hands-on activities helped children not only to establish the relationships between numbers and objects for subitising, but also understand the value of numbers.
Counting can benefit in a wide range of everyday situations. We do counting while using money. Even the housewives use this skill in the kitchen. They have to count the ingredients used in making various dishes. As I said before, counting is the base for all other math skills like addition, subtraction.
Overall, counting still plays a crucial role in many fields in the future. I do think children should be taught counting properly in early years to prepare for success in maths.

# Improved version
In my country, Mathematics is a compulsory subject from primary school. When I first started school, I learned basic skills such as addition, subtraction, multiplciation, and division. However, I would like to talk about counting, because it forms the foundation for all other mathematical operations.
