I find counting extremely useful in everyday life. For instance, we use counting when handling money, shopping, or even organizing daily tasks. Even in the kitchen, people need counting skills to measure and prepare ingredients properly. More importantly, counting is the basis of more advanced skills like addition and subtraction, so without it, learning higher-level maths would be very difficult.
In the future, I believe this skill will continue to benefit me. No matter what career path I choose, basic numerical ability is essential. Counting strenghthens logical thinking and accuracy, which are important in both academic and professional settings. That's why I think teaching children counting properly at an early age is crucial for their long-term success in Mathematics.
